<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>When the Fed reduces the money supply through open market operations, what is the sequence of effects?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Money supply ↓, interest rates ↑, investment ↑, AD ↑</option>
            <option letter="b">Money supply ↓, interest rates ↑, investment ↓, AD ↓</option>
            <option letter="c">Money supply ↓, interest rates ↓, investment ↑, AD ↑</option>
            <option letter="d">Money supply ↓, interest rates ↓, investment ↓, AD ↓</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>When the Fed reduces money supply by selling securities, it raises interest rates in the money market. Higher interest rates discourage borrowing and investment spending, which leads to a decrease in aggregate demand through the monetary policy transmission mechanism.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
